    <p>In this comparison review of two vape brands, <strong>VICE 5500</strong> emerges as the clear winner. Let's explore the detailed review of <strong>VICE 5500</strong> and its competitor, <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong>, based on the provided data:</p>

    <h2><strong>1. Puff Count:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE 5500</strong> offers an impressive puff count of <strong>5500</strong>, surpassing the <strong>2500</strong> puffs provided by the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong>. This substantial difference ensures that <strong>VICE 5500</strong> delivers an exceptionally longer-lasting vaping experience for users.</p>

    <h2><strong>2. E-liquid Capacity (ML):</strong></h2>

    <p>Both <strong>VICE 5500</strong> and the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> have the same e-liquid capacity of <strong>10 mL</strong>, ensuring users have ample e-liquid to enjoy their vaping sessions.</p>

    <h2><strong>3. Battery Capacity (mAh):</strong></h2>

    <p>The <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> boasts a larger battery capacity of <strong>1500 mAh</strong>, while <strong>VICE 5500</strong> offers a <strong>630 mAh</strong> capacity. Although the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> has a larger battery, the <strong>VICE 5500</strong> provides sufficient power for extended usage.</p>

    <h2><strong>4. Price and Cost Efficiency:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE 5500</strong> is competitively priced at <strong>$24.99</strong>, with a cost per milliliter of e-liquid at <strong>$2.50</strong>. In comparison, the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> is priced at <strong>$25.99</strong>, with a slightly higher cost per milliliter at <strong>$2.60</strong>. This cost efficiency makes <strong>VICE 5500</strong> a cost-effective choice for vapers.</p>

         <h2><strong>5. Release Date:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE 5500</strong> was released in <strong>Q4 2022</strong>, while the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> was released in <strong>Q3 2022</strong>, with only a slight difference in their release timing.</p>

    <h2><strong>6. Flavor Variety:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE 5500</strong> offers <strong>16</strong> flavors, providing a diverse range of options for users. In contrast, the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> offers <strong>15</strong> flavors.</p>

    <h2><strong>7. Rechargeable:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE 5500</strong> is rechargeable, offering users a more eco-friendly and cost-effective vaping solution. The <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong>, on the other hand, is not rechargeable.</p>

    <h2><strong>8. Special Features:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE 5500</strong> distinguishes itself with features such as a mesh coil, rechargeability, and sweet flavors. It caters to users looking for a sweet vaping experience. The <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> also features a mesh coil but lacks the rechargeable functionality.</p>

    <h2><strong>9. Flavor Profile:</strong></h2>

    <p><strong>VICE 5500</strong> is described as "<strong>very sweet</strong>," offering a delightful vaping experience. However, it's noted that the flavor drops off halfway through the usage. The <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> is described as "<strong>less sweet</strong>."</p>

    <p>In conclusion, based on the provided data and key factors, <strong>VICE 5500</strong> emerges as the superior choice. It offers a significantly higher puff count, competitive pricing, rechargeability, and a sweet flavor profile. While the <strong>ALLO Ultra 2500</strong> offers a larger battery capacity and a slightly lower cost per milliliter of e-liquid, it falls behind in puff count and rechargeability. <strong>VICE 5500</strong> is the top pick for vapers seeking a budget-friendly, flavorful, and long-lasting vaping experience, despite the flavor drop-off noted during usage.</p>
